    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-level5",
      "rationale": "Formal code verification performed using the Method of Manufactured Solutions (MMS) for the incompressible RANS equations, species transport (hemolysis scalar), and the SST k-ω turbulence model. Observed order of accuracy (OOA) for velocity components: 1.97 (theoretical 2.0); for pressure: 1.94; for hemolysis scalar: 1.96. All OOA values within 3% of theoretical second-order convergence. Verification suite executed on three systematically refined grids with refinement ratio r = √2. Results archived in verification report VR-CODE-2024-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-error-level5",
      "rationale": "Grid convergence study conducted on four systematically refined meshes (2.1M, 6.8M, 21.4M, 67.2M cells) using the Grid Convergence Index (GCI) methodology per Celik et al. (2008). GCI for hemolysis index at worst-case operating point: GCI_fine = 0.8%, GCI_medium = 2.3%. Richardson-extrapolated HI used as reference. Asymptotic range confirmed (GCI_medium/r^p × GCI_fine ≈ 1.002). Production mesh (21.4M cells) selected; discretization uncertainty contribution to total UQ budget documented. Wall y+ maintained between 30–300 for all wall-adjacent cells; near-wall treatment validated."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-level5",
      "rationale": "Bench test conditions rigorously characterised and matched to simulation boundary conditions. Flow rates measured with Coriolis mass flow meter (±0.2% accuracy, NIST-traceable calibration). Rotational speed measured with optical encoder (±0.05% accuracy). Blood analogue fluid (37% glycerol-water) viscosity and density characterised at test temperature via Anton Paar rheometer and density meter (±0.1% accuracy). Temperature controlled to ±0.5°C throughout test. Inlet velocity profile measured by LDV; turbulence intensity characterised. All instrumentation calibration certificates current and archived. Uncertainty budget for each test condition boundary parameter documented in test report TR-BENCH-2024-003."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-level5",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics applied to all validation QoIs: hemolysis index, pump head, and velocity field. Statistical comparison using validation metric V (Oberkampf & Barone 2006) computed with propagated experimental and numerical uncertainties. For HI: V = 0.94 (target ≥ 0.90 for level 5). For pump head: V = 0.97. For velocity field: area-weighted V = 0.91. Hypothesis testing (Wilcoxon signed-rank) confirms no systematic bias (p > 0.05) for all QoIs. Comparison plots with uncertainty bars archived in validation report VR-OUTPUT-2024-002."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-level5",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI (normalised hemolysis index, RH) directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion and clinical risk endpoint. Traceability established from clinical haemolysis threshold (plasma-free haemoglobin < 0.1 g/dL per ISO 10993-4) through the modified power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al., calibrated by Zhang et al.) to the CFD scalar transport output. Secondary QoIs (pump head, velocity magnitude, turbulent shear stress) are mechanistically linked to the primary QoI via the hemolysis model inputs. Sensitivity analysis confirms that the chosen QoIs collectively capture ≥ 95% of total output variance. QoI selection documented and peer-reviewed in technical report TR-QOI-2024-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-level5",
      "rationale": "Validation activities conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — identical to the device geometry modelled in the COU. Blood analogue fluid properties matched to physiological blood viscosity and density within 3%. Operating conditions span the full CPB flow-speed envelope defined in the COU (2–6 LPM, 2500–3500 RPM). Validation hierarchy established: component-level (impeller passage PIV), subsystem-level (pump head), and system-level (hemolysis index) validations all completed. Extrapolation distance from validation conditions to COU conditions assessed as negligible. Validation relevance assessment documented in VR-RELEVANCE-2024-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-level5",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via scaled residuals (all < 1×10⁻⁶ for continuity, momentum, turbulence, and hemolysis scalar) and integral QoI monitors (pump head and HI monitored over last 500 iterations; variation < 0.05%). Double-precision arithmetic used throughout. Round-off error estimated as negligible relative to discretization error. Solver settings (relaxation factors, numerical schemes) documented and fixed across all production runs. Iterative convergence uncertainty contribution quantified per Celik (2005) and included in total UQ budget. Numerical solver error report NSE-2024-001 archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-level5",
      "rationale": "Simulation execution controlled by a validated workflow management system (Snakemake v7.3) with automated input file generation from a parameter database, eliminating manual transcription errors. Independent peer review of all simulation setups performed by a second qualified CFD engineer prior to execution (four-eyes principle). Checklist-based setup verification protocol applied to each simulation run (47-item checklist covering geometry, mesh, boundary conditions, solver settings, post-processing scripts). All deviations from standard setup documented and assessed. User training records current for all analysts. Use error assessment report UE-2024-001 archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-level5",
      "rationale": "Model form selection justified through systematic comparison of four turbulence closures (standard k-ε, RNG k-ε, SST k-ω, RSM) and two hemolysis model formulations (Giersiepen power-law, Bludszuweit stress-based) against the PIV and hemolysis bench datasets. SST k-ω with Zhang et al. modified power-law hemolysis model selected based on lowest validation metric error and physical consistency of near-wall turbulence prediction. Newtonian blood analogue assumption validated: shear-thinning effects negligible at CPB operating shear rates (> 100 s⁻¹, confirmed by rheometry). Model form uncertainty quantified via Bayesian model averaging across the two best-performing model combinations; contribution to total UQ budget documented. Model form assessment report MF-2024-001 archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-level5",
      "rationale": "All 11 uncertain model inputs characterised with probability distributions derived from measurement data or literature meta-analysis: fluid viscosity (normal, µ = 3.45 mPa·s, σ = 0.17 mPa·s), density (normal, µ = 1056 kg/m³, σ = 11 kg/m³), clearance gap (uniform, ±50 µm), inlet turbulence intensity (log-normal, µ = 5%, σ = 2.5%), hemolysis model constant C (normal, µ = 3.62×10⁻⁷, σ = 3.6×10⁻⁸), hemolysis exponent α (normal, µ = 2.416, σ = 0.24), rotational speed (normal, ±1%), outlet pressure (normal, ±2 mmHg), blood temperature (uniform, ±2°C), inlet velocity profile shape (discrete, 3 profiles), mesh resolution level (discrete, 3 levels). Input characterisation report MI-2024-001 with full uncertainty budget archived."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
